WEBVTT

00:06.639 --> 00:07.874
Hello Shoreline.

00:07.874 --> 00:11.378
And hello to everyone
watching from around the world.

00:12.112 --> 00:15.115
Excited to be back for this year's I/O!

00:15.115 --> 00:17.917
I think it's been an incredible year.

00:17.917 --> 00:21.121
We are taking a differentiated,
full stack approach

00:21.121 --> 00:25.025
to AI innovation. To understand the scale
at which people are adopting AI,

00:25.425 --> 00:28.061
there's another great proxy: Tokens.

00:28.061 --> 00:31.865
The fundamental units of data our models
processes, many representing

00:31.865 --> 00:33.366
a problem being solved.

00:33.366 --> 00:38.238
We were processing 9.7 trillion
tokens a month across the surfaces,

00:38.238 --> 00:39.506
and fast forward to today,

00:39.506 --> 00:43.943
that number has jumped seven times to 3.2
quadrillion tokens per month.

00:44.177 --> 00:47.580
We now have 13 products
with over a billion users each.

00:48.148 --> 00:51.451
Five of those
have more than 3 billion users.

00:51.918 --> 00:54.587
Our Gemini models are a big reason

00:54.587 --> 00:58.958
more people are using our products
and why they are using our products more.

00:59.359 --> 01:02.362
AI overviews now has over 2.5 billion

01:02.395 --> 01:05.565
monthly users,
and AI mode has been a revela-

01:05.632 --> 01:09.402
-revelation our biggest upgrade
to search ever. In just a year,

01:09.536 --> 01:13.706
it's already surpassed
1 billion monthly users. Last year at I/O,

01:13.740 --> 01:17.010
the Gemini app had 400 million monthly
active users.

01:17.210 --> 01:20.947
Today, we have surpassed
900 million, more than doubling in a year.

01:22.816 --> 01:23.550
People come

01:23.550 --> 01:26.553
to YouTube every day
to ask a lot of questions.

01:26.619 --> 01:29.923
Ask YouTube entirely reimagines
the experience.

01:30.457 --> 01:33.793
Say you want to teach your three year
old how to ride a pedal bike,

01:33.793 --> 01:36.796
and they already know
how to ride a balance bike.

01:37.030 --> 01:39.732
Just Ask YouTube.

01:39.732 --> 01:42.669
With Docs Live,
you can just verbally brain dump

01:42.669 --> 01:45.905
whatever is on your mind
and let Gemini do the rest.

01:45.905 --> 01:49.109
So I just remembered I'm
doing an alumni talk tomorrow.

01:49.142 --> 01:51.111
I need to come up with some talking points
to explain

01:51.111 --> 01:53.079
what I do for a living
as a software engineer.

01:53.079 --> 01:55.949
Can you just pull my resume from drive?

01:55.949 --> 01:58.384
Although that might be boring. Umm.

01:58.384 --> 01:58.785
Maybe

01:58.785 --> 02:01.054
can you come up with some funny analogies?

02:01.054 --> 02:04.057
Oh, and also,
I think the school sent me an email.

02:04.190 --> 02:07.227
Maybe just grab the details from there,
throw them at the top of the doc

02:07.227 --> 02:09.262
so I know where to go
and what time to get there.

02:11.464 --> 02:12.132
We have taken a

02:12.132 --> 02:15.135
fundamentally different approach
with our training infrastructure.

02:15.301 --> 02:19.572
With JAX and Pathways, we can now
seamlessly distribute training across

02:19.572 --> 02:24.577
multiple sites, scaling across
more than 1 million TPUs globally.

02:24.811 --> 02:29.315
This gives us the ability to create
the largest training cluster in the world.

02:29.349 --> 02:32.619
To give you a live sense
of what the speed feels like,

02:32.852 --> 02:35.855
here's
a prompt on an upcoming Flash model,

02:36.055 --> 02:39.292
if it were running on 8I. I'll ask it

02:39.292 --> 02:42.395
to create a Chrome Dino game, push submit.

02:42.462 --> 02:46.866
The response is generated in real time.
As you watch,

02:47.033 --> 02:50.770
take a look at the tokens
per second in the top right corner.

02:51.237 --> 02:55.875
The speed is pretty incredible,
nearly 1500 tokens per second.

02:56.643 --> 03:00.947
It almost took longer
to write out the request, and the game is

03:00.947 --> 03:02.782
pretty fun too.

03:02.782 --> 03:05.118
There are three areas
where I want to go deeper today

03:05.118 --> 03:10.323
to show you the progress
in each: models, coding, and agents.

03:10.690 --> 03:13.693
I'm excited to announce Gemini Omni.

03:14.394 --> 03:18.264
Our new model
that can create anything from any input.

03:18.498 --> 03:22.035
It combines Gemini's intelligence
with the best of our generative

03:22.035 --> 03:27.640
media models for a new level of world
understanding, multimodality and editing.

03:27.740 --> 03:30.777
It's starting with video, but over time, Omni

03:30.777 --> 03:34.480
will be able to generate any output
from any input.

03:34.914 --> 03:39.752
As generative AI gets better,
so does the need for greater transparency.

03:40.119 --> 03:45.592
Since launch, SynthID has now watermarked
over 100 billion images and videos.

03:45.658 --> 03:50.663
We want more people to have easy access
to these tools, so we are expanding

03:50.663 --> 03:55.435
both SynthID and content credentials
verification to Search and Chrome.

03:55.501 --> 03:59.372
I'm thrilled to announce that OpenAI,
Kakao and ElevenLabs

03:59.372 --> 04:01.174
are adopting SynthID too.

04:02.875 --> 04:03.243
Today,

04:03.243 --> 04:07.013
I'm excited to introduce Gemini 3.5 Flash,

04:07.513 --> 04:10.516
our first in a series of models-

04:12.352 --> 04:14.721
combining
frontier intelligence with action.

04:14.721 --> 04:19.592
When compared to 3.1 Pro,
Flash is better across the board.

04:19.592 --> 04:22.161
Almost all benchmarks. 3.5 Flash

04:22.161 --> 04:25.798
is a very capable model.
At the frontier

04:25.798 --> 04:30.069
and comparable to the best models,
but much, much faster.

04:30.236 --> 04:32.071
It's in a whole league of its own

04:32.071 --> 04:35.742
in the top right
quadrant. We've been using 3.5 Flash

04:35.975 --> 04:40.747
with the reimagined version of our agent
first development platform, Antigravity,

04:40.913 --> 04:43.916
and it's dramatically accelerated
how we build.

04:44.384 --> 04:48.054
So using the new Antiravity and Gemini
3.5 Flash,

04:48.187 --> 04:51.991
we ask for agents to take on
what we consider to be a highly complex

04:51.991 --> 04:56.429
and impressive task: Build a working
operating system from scratch.

04:57.196 --> 05:01.301
Over 12 hours, 93 subjects
working in parallel,

05:01.334 --> 05:07.173
made over 15,000 model requests
and processed 2.6 billion tokens to take

05:07.173 --> 05:11.678
an initially empty project to the core
of a functioning operating system.

05:12.178 --> 05:16.949
But clearly, this isn't a real
OS unless I can play Doom.

05:19.719 --> 05:20.820
Now, if I try running

05:20.820 --> 05:23.823
Doom right now, it just doesn't work.

05:23.823 --> 05:26.693
Turns out that the OS is currently missing
some necessary video

05:26.693 --> 05:28.294
and keyboard drivers.

05:28.294 --> 05:29.495
I have a prompt prepared.

05:29.495 --> 05:32.231
I'm going to paste it in.

05:32.231 --> 05:35.635
Antigravity ended up
doing a whole host of research, ended up

05:35.635 --> 05:39.639
writing over 100 lines of code, and then
finally built the operating system.

05:40.139 --> 05:42.709
Let's take a peek and see if it works.

05:42.709 --> 05:45.311
Moment of truth.

05:45.311 --> 05:48.314
Amazing.

05:50.917 --> 05:51.551
This was made

05:51.551 --> 05:54.554
possible by the new subagent teamwork capability.

05:54.654 --> 05:57.657
It's optimized Flash
to be not just four times,

05:57.657 --> 06:00.660
but 12 times faster in Antigravity.

06:01.027 --> 06:04.430
Gemini 3.5 Flash is available for everyone

06:04.430 --> 06:07.467
today across our products and APIs.

06:07.467 --> 06:10.470
We are also excited for 3.5 Pro.

06:10.770 --> 06:12.171
We're using it internally.

06:12.171 --> 06:13.973
It's showing great improvements.

06:13.973 --> 06:16.542
I know you can't wait
to get your hands on it.

06:16.542 --> 06:19.545
Give us until next month to get it to you.

06:19.779 --> 06:23.416
Gemini 3.5 and Antigravity are unlocking

06:23.416 --> 06:27.053
a new world of agents
and agentic capabilities.

06:27.353 --> 06:31.357
We are super focused on
bringing the power of agents safely

06:31.357 --> 06:35.461
and securely to consumers,
so that they work for everyone.

06:35.895 --> 06:38.331
Introducing Gemini Spark.

06:40.199 --> 06:40.666
It's your

06:40.666 --> 06:44.704
personal AI agent that helps
you navigate your digital life,

06:44.971 --> 06:48.941
taking action on your behalf
and under your direction.

06:49.509 --> 06:52.011
It runs on dedicated virtual machines

06:52.011 --> 06:55.281
on Google Cloud, and it's 24/7.

06:55.314 --> 06:58.317
And yes, you can close your laptop.

06:58.851 --> 07:01.254
It's powered by Gemini 3.5

07:01.254 --> 07:04.257
and the Google Antigravity harness,

07:04.290 --> 07:08.828
which allows it to perform long
running tasks easily in the background.

07:09.295 --> 07:13.466
Spark will integrate seamlessly
with tools, starting with our own

07:13.466 --> 07:17.336
and in the coming weeks,
with third party tools through MCP.

07:17.570 --> 07:19.505
We're planning a big block party.

07:19.505 --> 07:22.141
And you can see here
this is a pretty complex prompt.

07:22.141 --> 07:25.144
We want help grabbing all the RSVP's,

07:25.478 --> 07:27.747
keep a list of who's bringing what,

07:27.747 --> 07:30.683
remember to email those neighbors
who haven't signed up yet.

07:30.683 --> 07:35.621
And what's amazing here is
Spark will go through step

07:35.621 --> 07:39.992
by step and again work across the various
skills and apps that you have.

07:40.026 --> 07:43.963
So the first one here,
this is a live RSVP tracker,

07:43.963 --> 07:45.865
right in Google Sheets

07:45.865 --> 07:50.069
and Spark is amazing at just brain
dumping things on your mind.

07:50.136 --> 07:53.873
Create a document with the top things
my wife and I need to do for the kids

07:53.873 --> 07:55.775
before the end of the school year.

07:55.775 --> 07:58.711
We'll check in later, to see how it's doing.

07:58.711 --> 08:01.781
And now we're entering the next chapter
of Google Search.

08:02.281 --> 08:02.982
Where incredible

08:02.982 --> 08:05.451
AI features aren't just in Search,

08:05.451 --> 08:08.521
Google Search is AI Search through
and through.

08:08.788 --> 08:11.624
Now we're taking an exciting step
toward this vision.

08:11.624 --> 08:13.459
We will be able to create and manage

08:13.459 --> 08:17.430
multiple AI agents for your many tasks
right in search.

08:17.663 --> 08:18.831
To start,

08:18.831 --> 08:23.202
you can set information agents to work for
you 24/7n in the background,

08:23.302 --> 08:27.340
and these will work with and alongside
Gemini Spark to help you get more done.

08:27.540 --> 08:29.675
Say you're really into finance
and you want to know

08:29.675 --> 08:31.143
more about big biotech stocks,

08:31.143 --> 08:35.915
but you want to know with P/E's under
15, positive cash flows and low debt, right

08:35.915 --> 08:39.719
when it matters. It connects directly
to our real time finance data,

08:39.719 --> 08:43.389
so you get up to the second updates
on stock prices and insights

08:43.389 --> 08:46.392
on the market the moment it moves.

08:46.626 --> 08:50.997
Now, when it does, your agent sends you
an intelligent and synthesized update.

08:51.130 --> 08:54.867
It helps you understand what's going on,
so you can separate the signal from

08:54.867 --> 08:55.902
the noise.

08:55.902 --> 09:00.907
So search now has the ability to help you
create entire, custom,

09:00.907 --> 09:06.412
stateful experiences.
Tools, trackers, dashboards. They're

09:06.412 --> 09:10.716
especially awesome for those long running
tasks where you want to keep coming back.

09:10.750 --> 09:14.153
Search proactively offers
to build a weekend planner for me,

09:14.153 --> 09:17.356
and I've chosen to securely connect
Gmail, Photos, and Calendar.

09:17.356 --> 09:19.759
And boom, there
it is. Looks like it's ready.

09:19.759 --> 09:21.394
And below, it's got all of these cool

09:21.394 --> 09:24.897
restaurant reservations
and beautifully laid out on Maps.

09:25.531 --> 09:29.869
People shop across
Google over a billion times a day.

09:30.403 --> 09:33.739
Combine the scale of the shopping graph
with our advanced

09:33.739 --> 09:37.209
Gemini models,
and you get entirely new ways to shop.

09:37.243 --> 09:39.378
When it comes to agentic commerce,

09:39.378 --> 09:43.115
we are focused on delivering three key
building blocks.

09:43.115 --> 09:46.218
First, the Universal Commerce Protocol,

09:46.252 --> 09:50.356
or UCP for short.
Our second building block,

09:50.623 --> 09:55.695
the Agent Payments Protocol,
or AP2. Our final building block,

09:55.761 --> 09:59.498
The Universal Cart,
a truly intelligent shopping cart.

09:59.532 --> 10:04.270
The moment you add a product, your cart
goes to work for you in the background.

10:04.837 --> 10:08.474
Now, another game changer
is how it applies intelligent reasoning.

10:08.941 --> 10:11.944
Let's say you're building
your first custom PC.

10:12.345 --> 10:15.881
You see a motherboard with great reviews
and just add that to your cart.

10:15.982 --> 10:19.752
Now you already picked out a processor,
but what you didn't realize

10:19.785 --> 10:23.956
is that the processor needs a motherboard
with a different type of socket.

10:24.490 --> 10:28.260
Your cart catches this
for you and suggests an alternative

10:28.294 --> 10:31.297
preventing a problem
you didn't really see coming.

10:31.297 --> 10:34.300
Today has been a jam packed Gemini Day.

10:34.300 --> 10:39.238
We've completely redesigned the entire
experience with Neural Expressive.

10:39.438 --> 10:43.509
We're shipping the brand new Gemini
Omni model and 3.5

10:43.542 --> 10:49.682
Flash model with 3.5 Pro coming soon,
and you can now put Gemini to work.

10:49.715 --> 10:53.986
Thanks to new features like the Daily
Brief, it's a personalized digest

10:54.020 --> 10:57.823
that's designed to be your first stop
every morning, synthesizing

10:57.823 --> 11:01.994
information from across my inbox,
my calendar, my tasks.

11:01.994 --> 11:05.431
It's finding the most important things
for me to be aware of.

11:05.431 --> 11:07.066
And Gemini Spark.

11:07.066 --> 11:08.601
You'll remember
at the beginning of the show,

11:08.601 --> 11:11.270
we sent a few tasks off,
so let's go check in on them.

11:11.270 --> 11:14.440
This was our school year
planning checklist and I asked it,

11:14.440 --> 11:17.576
remember, to create a doc of all the things
I didn't want to forget between now

11:17.576 --> 11:20.346
and the end of the year.
And so I'll open this one up.

11:20.346 --> 11:24.183
And what's amazing about it is
it takes advantage of all the Google Docs

11:24.183 --> 11:27.353
formatting so I can immediately click in.

11:27.420 --> 11:30.990
Whether you're a designer,
an entrepreneur, or an artist,

11:31.257 --> 11:34.060
our products help
shrink the gap between the moment

11:34.060 --> 11:37.063
you have an idea
and the moment you create it.

11:37.730 --> 11:41.534
At its best, technology is a canvas
for human creativity.

11:41.801 --> 11:46.372
Introducing Google Pics, a new product
in Google Workspace.

11:47.273 --> 11:50.176
Pics is our image creation editing tool

11:50.176 --> 11:53.179
that helps you create just about anything

11:53.345 --> 11:55.815
with the creative controls you want.

11:55.815 --> 11:59.552
You can hover over an element
and click to remove it.

11:59.719 --> 12:03.456
You can resize an object
to fit the frame, add or edit

12:03.522 --> 12:08.160
text, and translate
all of it with just a few clicks.

12:08.227 --> 12:11.030
We launched Google Flow at I/O last year.

12:11.030 --> 12:14.033
Flow could only execute
one prompt at a time.

12:14.300 --> 12:18.771
Now, your agent can take multiple actions
all at once.

12:18.838 --> 12:22.341
It analyzes
what's happening in the image, concepts

12:22.341 --> 12:26.779
the most compelling angles, and then boom!

12:27.079 --> 12:30.583
A single image becomes 16 unique videos.

12:32.351 --> 12:33.052
Today

12:33.052 --> 12:36.055
I'm excited to announce
that our first audio

12:36.122 --> 12:39.091
glasses will arrive this fall.

12:39.759 --> 12:44.096
The world's leading electronics company,
Samsung, is building

12:44.163 --> 12:49.735
innovative new devices and experiences
that set the bar for the whole industry.

12:50.636 --> 12:54.507
And we've been working to bring the best
of Google to these glasses as well.

12:54.540 --> 12:58.377
These audio glasses have brought together
the world's top

12:58.377 --> 13:02.615
eyewear designers
at Gentle Monster and Warby Parker.

13:02.715 --> 13:05.918
They are designed to give you all-day
help with Gemini

13:05.951 --> 13:09.321
that is spoken into your ear privately,
rather

13:09.321 --> 13:12.291
than shown on a display.

13:12.591 --> 13:15.227
Gemini, can you actually put my usual order

13:15.227 --> 13:18.097
in at that coffee shop
we just talked about?

13:18.097 --> 13:18.664
Sure.

13:18.664 --> 13:22.735
I'll order you a nitro cold brew
for pickup from Coupa Cafe on DoorDash.

13:23.202 --> 13:27.573
Gemini is able to launch
apps like DoorDash, then click through

13:27.573 --> 13:32.378
all the different option screens
automatically to order her coffee.

13:32.411 --> 13:36.582
I have prepared your order
for the nitro cold brew from Coupa Cafe.

13:36.682 --> 13:39.652
Would you like to confirm? Yes, please.

13:40.252 --> 13:43.756
All of these advances
show the staggering pace of AI progress.

13:43.756 --> 13:44.890
It's incredible.

13:44.890 --> 13:49.461
We're in a moment of immense promise,
but also enormous responsibility.

13:49.995 --> 13:54.633
The whole reason I've worked on AI
my entire career, was because I saw it

13:54.633 --> 13:58.671
as the ultimate tool to advance science
and our understanding of the world.

13:58.938 --> 14:01.941
I'm excited to announce Gemini
for Science.

14:02.241 --> 14:07.146
It brings together a number of powerful
AI tools to help accelerate research.

14:07.279 --> 14:11.217
Our new labs prototypes streamline
daily scientific tasks,

14:11.350 --> 14:14.854
whether it's staying on top of newly
published papers, transforming

14:14.854 --> 14:19.091
research goals into usable code,
or generating new hypotheses.

14:19.258 --> 14:22.261
Google's cutting-edge
research and products will help unlock

14:22.294 --> 14:26.131
AGIs incredible potential
for the benefit of the entire world.

14:26.265 --> 14:29.935
This technology will be a force multiplier
for human ingenuity

14:29.935 --> 14:34.473
and usher in a new golden age
of scientific discovery and progress,

14:34.773 --> 14:38.077
improving the lives of everyone
everywhere.

14:38.210 --> 14:40.946
Thank you and enjoy the rest of Google I/O.
